There are a lot of new people here, so I figured I’d say hello and tell you a bit about myself ❤️
⠀
My name is Lauren but I go by Lo (mostly) and I’ve been living in NYC for 11 years. I can’t believe how quickly the last decade has gone by.
⠀
I’m an entrepreneur in the women’s wellness space and founded @lovewellness more than 8 years ago. I started the company because of my own health issues and self-advocacy journey. It turns out I was dealing with vitamin deficiencies and gut health issues - both easy to manage if you know that’s what you’re dealing with, but if you don’t you may have an experience similar to mine (trying out lots of bad products and hearing experts tell you “it’s just stress” more times than you can count).
⠀
With the help of some forward-thinking board certified doctors, dietitians, and food scientists I created Love Wellness to address a lot of common issues that are often stigmatized with real innovation based on science based, evidence backed research on women’s bodies. BTW - research in women’s bodies has lagged so far behind that one of the reasons you’re seeing a lot of new innovation in this category in the last few years is because research is finally happening … like, right now.
⠀
My team and I live and work in New York City and we do a flex WFH/office schedule. I love the days when I get dressed and go into work. I feel like I am contributing to positive change in those days. You can find us at Target, Ulta, Amazon and lovewellness.com
⠀
And some fun facts - I’m a September 29 Libra, Aquarius Rising, Leo Moon. The new moon in Aquarius is already feeling blessed after many challenging years.
⠀
The one thing I’m hoping to maintain this year is continued balance in my body. You can read all about this in my new book called “Love Yourself Well”. It’s an expert-backed guide and plan to help you heal your gut/brain/vagina - which is also what we specialize in at @lovewellness.
⠀
Thanks for saying hi ❤️

So less of a hot tip and more of a reminder bc it’s not like putting collagen into coffee is anything new … BUT … if you tend to skip breakfast like me and go straight for coffee only, adding collagen is a really easy way to get protein into your system in the morning. It helps you stay more full, keeps glucose more steady so the first thing you eat isn’t too cray cray because of a blood sugar drop and also helps benefits skin, joints, etc! 3 packets of @lovewellness Call Me Collagen has 12g of protein! Just mix into your coffee and go - and if you get your coffee on the way to work like me the packets are perfect because you can just put them in your pocket. #collagencoffee #lovewellness #proteinhacks

Really been working on my skin lately and wanted to share what I’ve been trying, tossing, and then possibly incorporating into my daily routine. I love beauty and skincare so much so I’m always open to new ideas, products, and technology!

✨ Trying ✨
• Eye cream for the first time ever! As I get older the skin around my eyes is thinning and needs moisturizer. My fave so far is @biossance squalane eye cream
• TRYING and failing to find a spf + eye cream for daytime that doesn’t sting my eyes. I’ve been looking for a SPF that doesn’t sting and leaves a nice finish for years and I still have yet to discover my most desired, holy grail skincare item. 
• @nira_skin Laser is an at-home laser I’ve been using for about 10 days now to tighten up my upper eyelid area and reduce wrinkles underneath my eyes. The before/afters on the site are incredible so I’m hoping for nice results!

😭 Tossing 😭 
• Harsh topical retinol products like tretinoin. I think with more/improved laser tech going mainstream we may start to move away from really harsh skincare for the face. I see amazing results from medical grade lasers at my friend @philiplotfimd plastic surgery practice for evening skin tone and reducing wrinkles and my skin doesn’t tolerate tretinoin so I’m tossing it and replacing with high tech treatments. 

✨ Incorporating ✨ 
• I got some tiny ice globes to reduce puffiness around the eyes and I love them so much I’m incorporating them into my daily routine!
• @skinfixinc dermatitis facebalm is such a soothing and calming balm that I’ve been loving during the colder months and while I do allergy immunotherapy, so this one wins a spot in my beauty cabinet!
• Aura and Cool Touch Lasers are medical grade lasers for skin; I’ve been going to the doc for treatments every few weeks since summer and I’ve seen the biggest transformation in my skin color, texture, etc! I’m a laser girlie forever now.

When I started to share my health issues with the world back in 2016 I never imagined as a result I’d end up in a room with the likes of Selena Gomez, Patrick Ta, Gucci Westman and power players like Walmart and Amazon. But, that’s what happened today at the @wwd #BeautyInc Awards. 

Not only did I have the honor of attending and hearing from so many shining stars of the beauty world, we joined the ranks of past winners by earning the award of BRAND OF THE YEAR in the Wellness category.

My original vision for Love Wellness when I started this company was to make caring for health issues that have been stigmatized innovative, enjoyable, beautiful, fun, effective, and simple. As a beauty lover (my friends and family literally called my childhood bathroom “Lo’s Beauty Palace” and would schedule “appointments”) I dreamt of daily self-care solutions that would make me feel the same type of excitement, hope, and joy that my favorite lip gloss would. Joy from a vaginal suppository? YES!

The entire @lovewellness team (a mighty 40) puts everything they’ve got into this incredible brand. We do it for women who love the brand, people who have no clue who we are/what we do but may benefit from how the education we share influences broader awareness on how women’s bodies work, and for future generations of kids who have the opportunity to think and feel differently about their bodies from a young age.

Thank you @WWD for the incredible support, to our customers, to our retail partners @walmart @target @ulta @amazon for taking a chance on us, and to all of you who have helped make Love Wellness the Wellness Brand of the Year.
